      <div  class="layout__region layout__region--second layout__region--wide layout__region--75">
        <div class="block-ps-accordion with-block-description block block-layout-builder block-inline-blockps-accordion" data-block-plugin-id="inline_block:ps_accordion">
  
      
  
  
  
      
      <div class="field field--name-field-ps-accordion field--type-ps-accordion field--label-hidden field__items">
              <div class="field__item"><div role="group" aria-label="accordion">
  <dl id="ps_accordionfield_ps_accordion_block_content_31"  data-expanded-default="false" class="ps-accordion" role="presentation">
          <dt class="ps-accordion-item ">
        <div role="heading" aria-level="3">
          <div  id="acc-btn" role="button" aria-controls="acc-panel" aria-expanded="false" tabindex="0" class="ps-accordion-item-button">
            <span class="indicator" aria-hidden="true"><span class="indicator-target"></span></span>
            Sponsored Research
          </div>
        </div>
      </dt>
      <dd class="ps-accordion-content">
        <div  id="acc-panel" role="region" aria-labelledby="acc-btn">
          <ul><li dir="ltr"><strong>Getting started with proposal development: </strong>Visit <a href="https://orpa.princeton.edu/sponsored-project-lifecycle/proposal-development">Princeton’s Office of Research &amp; Project Administration</a> (ORPA).</li><li dir="ltr"><strong>MAE staff should be notified of your intent to submit a proposal a minimum of 10 working days</strong> <strong>(two weeks) prior to the deadline</strong>. More than two weeks of notice is always preferred. The MAE business center will provide the Office of Research &amp; Project Administration (ORPA) with a monthly update of upcoming proposal submissions.</li></ul><p dir="ltr">Please note: some proposals may require extra time, such as those pertaining to sponsors, international agencies, sub-awards, or proposals with multi-PIs/institutions. To allow sufficient time for MAE staff and ORPA to complete their required reviews, <strong>please add extra time for these types of proposals.</strong></p><p dir="ltr">We understand that last minute proposal requests happen occasionally. To assist with MAE and ORPA workload planning, <strong>notices that do not meet the above guidelines will require a written exception by the Department Chair</strong>.&nbsp;In these rare instances, please write to your grants manager and to the department chair so that a determination about department support for submitting a last-minute proposal can be made.</p>
        </div>
      </dd>
          <dt class="ps-accordion-item ">
        <div role="heading" aria-level="3">
          <div  id="acc-btn--2" role="button" aria-controls="acc-panel--2" aria-expanded="false" tabindex="0" class="ps-accordion-item-button">
            <span class="indicator" aria-hidden="true"><span class="indicator-target"></span></span>
            Buying and Paying
          </div>
        </div>
      </dt>
      <dd class="ps-accordion-content">
        <div  id="acc-panel--2" role="region" aria-labelledby="acc-btn--2">
          <p dir="ltr">All order requests should be emailed to&nbsp;<a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#bacacfc8d9d2dbc9d3d4dde5d7dbdffacac8d3d4d9dfced5d494dfdecf"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="3f4f4a4d5c575e4c56515860525e5a7f4f4d56515c5a4b5051115a5b4a">[email&#160;protected]</span></a> and your assigned purchasing contact will manage your request.</p><ul><li dir="ltr">Reference materials for<a href="https://finance.princeton.edu/how-to/buying-paying/"> buying &amp; paying for goods and services&nbsp;</a>can be found in the Information and Training button on the PRIME portal.</li><li dir="ltr">Create a cart or non-catalog order and route to your purchasing specialist.</li><li dir="ltr">Other quotes can be sent to&nbsp;<a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#91e1e4e3f2f9f0e2f8fff6cefcf0f4d1e1e3f8fff2f4e5feffbff4f5e4"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="97e7e2e5f4fff6e4fef9f0c8faf6f2d7e7e5fef9f4f2e3f8f9b9f2f3e2">[email&#160;protected]</span></a></li><li dir="ltr">Laboratory supplies should not be out-of-pocket expenses unless in emergency situations and please be prepared to provide the necessary backup.</li><li dir="ltr">Computers cannot be purchased on a personal or University credit card - always route the requests through the marketplace. <a href="https://finance.princeton.edu/policies/computer-equipment-policy#:~:text=Computers%20must%20be%20purchased%20via,personal%20or%20University%20credit%20cards.">See the computer policy&nbsp;here</a>.</li></ul>
        </div>
      </dd>
          <dt class="ps-accordion-item ">
        <div role="heading" aria-level="3">
          <div  id="acc-btn--3" role="button" aria-controls="acc-panel--3" aria-expanded="false" tabindex="0" class="ps-accordion-item-button">
            <span class="indicator" aria-hidden="true"><span class="indicator-target"></span></span>
            Travel and Expenses (Concur)
          </div>
        </div>
      </dt>
      <dd class="ps-accordion-content">
        <div  id="acc-panel--3" role="region" aria-labelledby="acc-btn--3">
          <p dir="ltr">Travel and expense reimbursements are submitted through&nbsp;<a href="https://travel.princeton.edu/">Concur</a> and should include the required information. Multiple, unrelated expenses may be included on a single expense report. Please do not route multiple reports with a single item on each report.</p><ul><li dir="ltr">As per the travel and business expense policies, expenses must be routed within 30 days from the date of the transaction. Do not wait to route advance expenses (hotel deposit, airfare, registration) after your trip or they may be counted as taxable income.</li><li dir="ltr">Concur can be accessed from the&nbsp;<a href="http://prime.princeton.edu/">PRIME portal</a> or&nbsp;<a href="http://travel.princeton.edu">travel.princeton.edu</a>.</li><li dir="ltr">More information:&nbsp;<a href="https://finance.princeton.edu/policies/travel-policy">Travel</a></li><li dir="ltr">More information:&nbsp;<a href="https://finance.princeton.edu/policies/business-expense-policy">Business Expenses</a></li><li dir="ltr"><a href="https://travel.princeton.edu/faculty-staff/expense-how-tos">Concur Expense How-Tos</a></li><li dir="ltr">IMPORTANT: You must assign an expense approver before you can route a report through Concur. Your Concur approver is your supervisor or faculty advisor and the faculty assistant is your expense delegate.&nbsp; Contact a faculty assistant for assistance.</li><li dir="ltr">You MUST complete the Business Purpose for each line item. It should always answer Who/What/Where/When and Why. Example: You have a meal expense, your last name should be first such as: Smith/meal/talk @ APS Mtg/SanDiego/Nov2019</li></ul>
        </div>
      </dd>
      </dl>
</div>
</div>
